**The coffee tree is a small tree, about 3 to 4 meters tall, with dense foliage and a relatively symmetrical shape. The leaves of the coffee plant are oval and pointed, dark green with a slight reddish brown or purple color depending on the variety. The leaves of the coffee tree are arranged symmetrically on the branches and are quite thick, giving a dense appearance to the foliage. The coffee plant grows abundantly in the tropics and has small white flowers that are produced in clusters. These inflorescences will then develop into coffee berries, which are round or ovoid in shape and green when ripe. On the trunk of the coffee tree, many branches grow, creating a risky and diverse appearance for the tree. On the tops of mature coffee trees, coffee cherries will bloom symmetrically on the branches, creating a natural beauty and attracting the attention of the beholder.** - Upscaled by <@1079236530591252512> (fast)
